		   <table class="mform"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top">
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Tue, Mar 13th 2:37 PM 2001 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class=sm>IP: Logged</span> | <a class=sm href="/db/classes.html?class=6&mid=98445804515670&num=2&post=1&replyto=98451226029496"><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=11 width=17> Reply to this</a></a>   <a name=98451226029496></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=2048"><span id=Sage>SouldragoonFlamingheart</span></a><b><span id=Sage><br>Sage</span></b><br><img src=/shared/user_star_ico.gif height=9 width=9><br>144 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [4.60]</nobr><br><br><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>I have an enchanter that I use for my trade skills.&nbsp;&nbsp;I got pretty sick and tired of trying to skill up my pally with his gawd awful wisdom and intelligence.  Was genuinely surprised at how much faster my high elf chanter skilled up... 113 skill in 5 hours compared to the month it took my dumb paladin to make 60 skill.<br><br>Anyways, here's what you want to do.  Do NOT invest any skill points into smithing.  You would only be able to invest 20 points max, and the first 20 are the easiest and cheapest to make through practice.  In north freeport, groflah's forge sells all of the smithing supplies that you will need.  Buy a few stacks of sharpening stones and take them to east freeport.  Down an alleyway, that runs next to the trader's holiday, you will find a store called hallard's resales.  He sells rusty weapons.  I must forewarn you, tho, do NOT go down the stairs in this shop.  Doing so will cause his dog scraps to come out and bite your leg off.  (Though at level 32, you could probably kill him, but you never know if doing so would get you into a fight with his owner...)  Take a few bags of rusty daggers over to the forge which is next to the armor shop in the zone.  Combine one sharpening stone and one dagger until you run out of stones.  Sell the tarnished daggers back and buy more rusty ones.  This should get you all the way up to skill 21.<br><br>Next, go back to north freeport, and buy a pack full of water.  (yes, 8 stacks of 20).  Then go back to groflah's and buy 2 packs of small ore.  (The stackable ore, yes, 16 stacks of 20).  =P  Go use the forge outside of Groflahs and combine 1 water and 2 ore to make a metal bit (the basic componant in many other smithing recipes).  Make sure each ore is in it's own slot in the forge before combining.  One tip to help make this a hella lot easier on you...  <b>Use the ctrl key when you left click on a stack to only select 1 out of the stack.. </b>so that you don't have to mess with that annoying slider bar to pick how many you want.  If you need to use another forge, cuz this one is being used, there is another one near the bank.<br><br>Once you have finished making as many metal bits as possible from this, go buy more water.  It'll be easier on you if you buy the same amount of water as you have metal bits.  Also, to maximize your efficiency, have 6 backpacks in your inventory, and leave 2 empty slots.  You will want to place a stack of bits and a stack of water in those 2 empty slots.  You will find out why once you start smithing.  =P  You can only have 2 bags open at any one time, and the forge counts as a bag.  You will want a bag open in your inventory, that contains the molds you will be using.<br><br>Fill up all the extra space in your bags with scaler molds.  You can buy molds from the trader's holiday.  Combine 1 scaler mold, 1 metal bit, and 1 water to create a file.  This used to create a file and a large container mold, but has been fixed in a patch.  (boohoo)  You will skill out with scalers at, I believe, skill 34.<br><br>The next step will be to make lantern casings.  To make a lantern casing, you will need to combine 1 lantern casing mold, 1 metal bit, 1 water, and 1 bottle.  Bottles can be also be bought from the trader's holiday, from the bartenders.  You will skill out with lantern casings somewhere in the 50's... I think it was 54.<br><br>You still won't quite be able to make banded just yet... almost there...<br><br>This is the point that gets super boring..  Making skewers.  It will, however, get you all the way up to about 113 skill.  (which is where it has just capped with my chanter)  To make a skewer, you will need to combine 1 skewer mold, 1 metal bit, and 1 water.  You will fail ALOT, but your skill will still go up with failures, as usual.  By the time you skill out with this, you will be able to make several pieces of banded, and the tougher pieces of banded on just a few attempts.  (you will also need to make banded to continue skilling up)<br><br>For the recipes on banded armor, just look em up in the skills section of this site.  There is a handy recipe list there that I still use.  I've invested, so far, 100 pp in obtaining 113 skill.  Hope this helps ya out.<br><br>Souldragoon Flamingheart<br>45th circle Paladin of Virtue<br>Fennin Ro</p><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br><i>Follow virtue, and the virtuous will follow you.</i></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >0 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td class=mhback align=right><span class=mh id=fs8><a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=6><img src=/shared/root_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Up" width=17 height=11> Thread Index</a> |  <a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=6&post=1><img src=/shared/new_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="New" width=17 height=11> New Subject</a> | <a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=6&mid=98445804515670&num=2&post=1&mid=98445804515670><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply" width=17 height=11> Reply to Thread</a></span></td></tr><tr><td><table width=100% border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 class=mform><tr><td colspan=1  style='font-size: 9.5px;'>2 Posts [ <a href="/fsearch.html?base=class6">Search Forums</a> ]</nobr></td></tr></table>&nbsp;</td></tr>
